Pretest
Personality traits were measured with the Big Five Inventory-2. The BFI measures the five broad domains of personality and three more specific facets for each trait. In addition, the responsibility facet from Roberts' 2005 measure of conscientiousness and the dutifulness facet from the NEO-PI-3 were administered. 

Covariates are self-reported age, gender, race, and education for the primary analyses. In a supplementary model, we will add income as an additional covariate.

Posttest
Behavioral responses related to the COVID-19 pandemic include:
(1) concerns about contracting the coronavirus or the effects of the pandemic on finances and relationships;
(2) precautions taken to avoid catching the coronavirus (wash hands often; use hand sanitizer; avoid touching your eyes, nose, and mouth; put distance between yourself and other people (social distancing); wear a face mask; clean and disinfect surfaces);
(3) preparatory behaviors related to the pandemic (I bought face masks; I stocked up on hand sanitizer; I stocked up on toilet paper; I stocked up on food and/or drinks; I changed my travel plans because of the coronavirus);
(4) duration estimates for the time until the outbreak is controlled, the social quarantine ends, society goes back to normal, the participant recovers from financial losses, and the US recovers from financial losses.

Further variables such as loneliness and other mental health indicators, were also measured but were not included in these analyses. See pretest survey and posttest survey for all measures administered.

